Template: filezilla-server/admin-password
Type: password
Default:
Description: Please input the administrator password:
 An administration password is highly suggested, to protect your system from the risk that any users or program that has access to it could make changes to FileZilla Server and potentially gain root privileges.
 .
 Leave it blank if you really don't want to use a password, but in that case you'll not be able to administer FileZilla Server remotely. 

Template: filezilla-server/no-admin-password-provided
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you still want to proceed without an administration password?
 No administration password has been provided, this is dangerous.
 .
 Without an administration password, any user and any program on your computer will be able to make changes to FileZilla Server and potentially gain root privileges on the machine FileZilla Server is running on.

Template: filezilla-server/default-impersonator-user
Type: string
Default: ftp
Description: Please input the system account name for accessing files and directories (leave empty to not make use of this functionality):
 FileZilla Server can make use of a system account to provide access to the file system, to those users who log in without system credentials or without explicitly using their system credentials to access files and directories. 
 .

Template: filezilla-server/default-impersonator-group
Type: string
Default:
Description: Please input the system group name for accessing files and directories (leave empty to make use of the default one):
 FileZilla Server can make use of a system group to provide access to the file system, to those users who log in without system credentials or without explicitly using their system credentials to access files and directories. 
 .

Template: filezilla-server/x-reconfiguring
Type: boolean
Default: false

Template: filezilla-server/config-version-error
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you want to make a backup of the files and continue? Choosing No will abort the installation.
 One or more existing configuration files belong to a version of FileZilla Server which is not guaranteed to be compatible.
 .
 FileZilla Server can still load them up, but some information might be lost.
 .

